-- Sprint eyes up to $800 million labor savings in '08
-- 
-- Mon May 12, 2008 8:46am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/12/us-sprint-jobs-idUSN1220658020080512

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Wireless service provider Sprint Nextel Corp said on Monday it expects labor-related savings of $700 million to $800 million in 2008. 

 The company also said on a conference call with analysts it completed its plans to cut 4,000 jobs. (Reporting by  Sinead Carew ; Editing by  Derek Caney )